<sect2 id="sect_definingDBElements" label="2">
    <title id="title_definingDBElements">Defining DB elements in a form</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>The groups of a form visually group the data of their ancor <glossterm
                                linkend="tableAlias">table alias</glossterm>. The data itself is
                            displayed within <glossterm linkend="DBElement">DB elements</glossterm>
                            such as textfields, checkboxes, etc. that are directly tied to a table
                            field of the ancor <glossterm linkend="tableAlias">table alias</glossterm>.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>DB Elements</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>
                            <guibutton>DB Elements</guibutton> are GUI elements tied directly to a
                            table field of the ancor <glossterm linkend="tableAlias">table alias</glossterm>.</para>
                        <para>The following <guibutton>DB Elements</guibutton> exist: </para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Text</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can show table fields of the type text, integer. long, float,
                                    double and decimal. </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Long text</guimenuitem> fields and
                                        <guimenuitem>Long text dialog</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can display table fields of the type longtext.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Checkbox</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can show table fields of the type integer and long modelled as
                                    boolean like table fields.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Combobox</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can display table fields of the type enum.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Time</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can show table fields of the type time.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Date</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can display table fields of the type date.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Timestamp</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can show table fields of the type timestamp.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Image</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can show table fields of the type binary or document.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Document</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can display table fields of the type document.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                        <para>The definition of the <glossterm linkend="DBElement">DB elements</glossterm>
                            <guimenuitem>Foreign field</guimenuitem> and <guimenuitem>Table
                            view</guimenuitem> will be explained in the following sections.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Procedure</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para> Proceed the following steps to define a <glossterm
                                linkend="DBElement">DB element</glossterm> in a group:</para>
                        <para>
                            <informaltable rowsep="1" colsep="1" frame="all">
                                <tgroup cols="2">
                                    <colspec align="center" colwidth="1*"/>
                                    <colspec align="left" colwidth="6*"/>
                                    <thead>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>Step</entry>
                                            <entry align="center">Procedure</entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>1</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Load the form containing the group to be
                                                  edited into the form editor.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>2</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Select the desired DB element from the
                                                  <guibutton>DB Elements</guibutton> menu in
                                                  the form editor.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>3</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Place the DB element at the desired
                                                  position in the group edited by pressing the
                                                  left mouse button.</para>
                                                <para>As already explained above, DB elements are
                                                  always assigned to a table column. Therefore,
                                                  <trademark>jACOB</trademark> Designer will pop
                                                  up a dialog asking you for the appropriate table
                                                  column. <trademark>jACOB</trademark> Designer
                                                  lists a priori only the table columns of the
                                                  groups ancor table alias that can be displayed
                                                  in the DB element selected.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>4</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Specify the appropiate table column and
                                                  confirm your input.</para>
                                                <para>Hereafter, <trademark>jACOB</trademark>
                                                  Designer will automatically create the
                                                  appropriate label. <trademark>jACOB</trademark>
                                                  Designer retrieves the string from the column object.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </tbody>
                                </tgroup>
                            </informaltable>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect2>
